;; run_parity — the INTERPRETED entry for the parity harness. `cljgo run`
;; evaluates a file's top-level forms but does not call -main (that is the
;; compiled binary's job), so this thin runner requires app.parity and
;; calls it. The compiled side builds app.parity directly (its func main
;; invokes -main). Both drive the SAME app.parity / app.routes code.
(require '[app.parity :as p])
(p/-main)
